    @Namespace(value="nvinfer1")
 @NoOffset

public class IIteratorLayer
extends ILoopBoundaryLayer
    \class IIteratorLayer \brief A layer to do iterations. The iterator layer iterates over a tensor along the given axis and in the given direction. It enables each loop iteration to inspect a different slice of the tensor.
    See Also:
    ILoop::addIterator()

      • setReverse

        @NoException(value=true)
public void setReverse(@Cast(value="bool")
                                                 boolean reverse)
        \brief Set iteration order to be reverse. For reverse=false, the layer is equivalent to addGather(tensor, I, 0) where I is a scalar tensor containing the loop iteration number. For reverse=true, the layer is equivalent to addGather(tensor, M-1-I, 0) where M is the trip count computed from TripLimits of kind kCOUNT. The default is reverse=false.
